{quote}
Our bamboo server failed to run the scheduled backup (things happen!). I have rerun the backup and it successfully passed.

However, the error message doesn't seem to disappear - is there a way to clear it out? It's showing as a yellow alert box on the top of each page in Bamboo.

 

// side issue there looks to be an odd css problem in the last update of chrome, so its hovering over the menu links - hence the desire to clear out the error :)
{quote}

Go to https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO/Polling+the+repository+for+changes and scroll to the bottem. There appears the following error
{noformat}
Error rendering macro 'gallery' : com/atlassian/confluence/plugins/macros/advanced/GalleryMacro$1
{noformat}

This URL:
{noformat}
git@host.com:magicalpanda/AtlassianTestRepo.git
{noformat}
will be ok for git, but it will fail with Bamboo because it will try to push it through proxy and to do that, it will add port. Port is not allowed with SCP notation in Git.
The workaround for this is to use an URL with username expansion:
{noformat}
git@host.com:~/magicalpanda/AtlassianTestRepo.git
{noformat}

I have a plan with multiple stages and jobs. When I try to clone this plan, the resulting plan does not show any requirement for its jobs. Instead, the list is empty.

In fact, the requirements seems to be there, since I cannot add capabilities with keys defined in the parent plan, but I can add capabilities which are not used on the parent plan.

The description of the requirements also shows something weird:
{noformat}
This job can only be built by agents whose capabilities meet the {0} below. One agent is capable of building this Job.
{noformat}

In our [documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO40/PostgreSQL+8.2] on installing Bamboo on specific databases, we do mention the following in the case of Postgres:
{quote}
Please note, the JDBC driver for PostgreSQL 8.2 (PostgreSQL Driver 8.4.x) is bundled with Bamboo. You do not have to download and install the driver.
{quote}

Many users assume with the above information that the JDBC is bundled in all distributions. It will be nice if we can add an additional info to that comment.

Instead of: 
{quote}
Merging disabled: your Default Repository type does not support Branch merging.
{quote}
Return a more constructive/explicit Error message when JGit is used in automatic branch merging, when only a native Git can be used.
